```{r}
#| include = FALSE
knitr::opts_chunk$set(
  collapse = TRUE,
  fig.path = "fig-vignettes-scatter-plots-",
  fig.cap = "",
  fig.width = 11,
  fig.height = 8,
  fig.retina = 2,
  dpi = 300,
  comment = "#>",
  dev = "ragg_png"
)
```

```{r}
library(manCTMed)
```

## Population Total, Direct, and Indirect Effects

Total, direct, and indirect effects for the drift matrix

\begin{equation}
    \left(
    \begin{array}{ccc}
         -0.357 & 0 & 0 \\
         0.771 & -0.511 & 0 \\
         -0.450 & 0.729 & -0.693 \\
    \end{array}
    \right)
\end{equation}

```{r, effects}
FigPlotEffects()
```

## Evaluation of Confidence Intervals

Presented below are scatter plots of coverage probabilities and power for the $\eta_X \to \eta_M \ to \eta_Y$ model and type I error rates for the $\eta_Y \to \eta_M \to \eta_X$ model.

```{r}
data(results, package = "manCTMed")
```

### Coverage Probabilities

#### Time-Intervals 1 to 25

```{r, coverage-1-25}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotCoverage(results, delta_t = 1:25)
```

#### Time-Intervals 1 to 4

```{r, coverage-1-4}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotCoverage(results, delta_t = 1:4)
```

#### Time-Intervals 5 to 25

```{r, coverage-5-25}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotCoverage(results, delta_t = 5:25)
```

#### Time-Intervals 25 to 30

```{r, coverage-25-30}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotCoverage(results, delta_t = 25:30)
```

### Statistical Power

```{r, power}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotPower(results)
```

### Type I Error Rate

```{r, type1}
#| echo = FALSE,
#| cache = FALSE
FigScatterPlotType1(results)
```
